ann m fudge  wikipedia ann m fudge from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search ann marie fudge born april   serves on a number of corporate boards including those of general electric novartis unilever and infosys as well as on several nonprofit boards she is former chairman and ceo of young  rubicam brands a global network of marketing communications companies in  fudge served on president barack obamas national commission on fiscal responsibility and reform contents  early life and education  career  political involvement and public service  personal life  awards and honors  references  external links early life and educationedit fudge was born and raised in washington dc and attended the citys catholic schools through th grade she cited the riots she lived through after the assassination of the rev dr martin luther king jr as a hurtful but formative experience they made me incredibly determined she said i wanted to do something that black people hadnt done before when i hit roadblocks that was what kept me going  she grew up middle class in washington the first of two children born to a mother who was a manager at the national security agency and a father who was an administrator at the postal service they stressed education  and fudge also credits the nuns for pushing her to do her best fudge is a graduate of simmons college and harvard business school earning respectively ba honors in retail management  and mba  in  hbs prof stephen a greyser recalled fudge as a solid citizen a solid student discussing her educational choices with business week in  she said when i was at simmons college i had this great professor  margaret hennig she was the one who encouraged me to think about business and apply to harvard business school she and ann jardim wrote the first book on women in business called the managerial woman and founded the simmons graduate school of business i applied to harvard business school my senior year careeredit one job fudge had while still in high school was with the teen board at hechts department store the job included advising on teenage fashions and a trip to fashion magazines in new york after college fudge worked in the human resources department of the general electric company before pursuing her mba after harvard fudge spent nine years at general mills her biggest accomplishment there she said was her part as a marketing assistant on the team that developed honey nut cheerios today its one of the nations biggest cereal brands fudge then served ultimately as president of the beverages desserts and post division a  billion unit of kraft foods at kraft she served on the management committee and managed many businesses including maxwell house coffee gevalia kaffe koolaid crystal light post cereals jello desserts and altoids in  fudge was named by fortune magazine as th on the  most influential women in american business list carly fiorina  oprah winfrey  while she was executive vice president at kraft at the time coffee and cereals for which fudge was responsible accounted for  billion  of krafts  billion in sales she also at the time sat on the boards of alliedsignal liz claiborne both as of  and catalyst inc in  after a year as president of the beverages et al division at kraft fudge decided to retire she related to business week that her choice to leave kraft was based on a number of reasons she had had a goal of retiring before age  she had dealt with the recent illness and death of her parents some close friends and relatives to be honest i still havent figured it out  it was definitely not dissatisfaction it was stepping back and saying what are you really here for what do you really want to accomplish she spent two years reconnecting with friends and family and delving into community work her charitable work included work with a number of organizations including the executive leadership council a nonprofit group of highlevel africanamerican leaders in business the boys and girls club of america partnership for a drugfree america and the united way among others from her time away fudge became inspired by the power individuals have to make a difference in the world following the sabbatical fudge served as chair and chief executive officer of young  rubicam brands from  to  in  business week summed up some of the challenges facing her saying yr has suffered through poor management and a messy merger in recent years the various units tend to work in isolation the ad agency has lost some big clients and employees are disgruntled  including reports of animosity between fudge and creative head michael patti fudge was inside the boardroom guest  carlson school of management at the university of minnesota in february  fudge was featured by the commonwealth institute in miami florida and in april  fudge spoke at the economic club of minnesota as of  fudge served on the boards of directors of general electric novartis and unilever she also served as chair of the us programs advisory board of the gates foundation and she was a trustee of the rockefeller foundation brookings institution the council on foreign relations and morehouse college she has been a morehouse trustee since april  she has also served on the board of buzzient inc and served as vice chair of the harvard board of overseers in june  it was announced that fudge would join the board of indian technology and outsourcing company infosys on october   as an additional director fudge was at the time the sole woman on the board and was recruited by retiring founder nr narayana murthy and nominations committee chair jeffrey s lehman murthy had served also on the unilever board and knew fudge from there in september  fudge was one of six hall of fame honorees named in advance of the national association of corporate directors november gala in new york city political involvement and public serviceedit in  fudge was a member of the obama presidential campaign’s finance committee in early  fudge was named by president obama to the member national commission on fiscal responsibility and reform a bipartisan panel chaired by former senator alan k simpson rwy and former white house chief of staff erskine bowles d the balance of the panel was three more members appointed by the president six members of the us house of representatives and six members of the us senate the commission first met on april   and had a december report deadline though specific actions based on the report were limited commission members who were also members of congress reappeared in the socalled gang of six in spring and summer  in the debtceilingincrease debate in september  fudge was listed as one of several possible candidates to replace larry summers as director of the national economic council some reports signalled that the white house could be looking for a female executive with business experience to fill the post in september  fudge joined in the committee for a responsible federal budget crfb go big forum crfb along with the new america foundation the concord coalition and the bipartisan policy center discussed the path ahead for the joint select committee on deficit reduction super committee and the reasons it should exceed its mandate fudge also serves on the state departments foreign affairs policy board personal lifeedit as a sophomore at simmons ann married rich fudge before she graduated they had a baby rich jr she had to balance personal and academicprofessional demands from that early stage on her fondest memory from general mills  involved her younger son kevin then  ms fudge had just been made a marketing director the first woman and the first black at that level i came home all excited and was telling my family and he said whats the big deal mom so now instead of one brand you have four you can do that he was right my sons have helped keep things in perspective fudge is also noted for having pursued her career despite the glass ceiling which has been seen to thwart promotion to the top ranks facing women and minorities in the corporate workforce particularly and in regards fudges relatively early moves out of jobs the  business week article also included a sidebar on four other women who left highpowered positions in the corporate world to find a place where they could work on their own terms fudge is currently based in chestnut hill ma she and her husband have five grandchildren awards and honorsedit candace award national coalition of  black women  referencesedit  a b c d ann fudge biography jrankorg retrieved june    a b c d e f g way beyond the glass ceiling by judith h dobrzyski the new york times may   retrieved june   via jrankorg bio  a b c president obama appoints morehouse trustee ann fudge to fiscal commission archived june   at the wayback machine morehouse press release by add seymour jr march   retrieved june    a b ann fudge on making choices the young  rubicam ceo talks about the benefits of stepping away from work and how her priorities changed because of it archived december   at the wayback machine interview with diane brady also act two cover image of ann fudge archived december   at the wayback machine a family portrait archived december   at the wayback machine an assessment of six young  rubicam operations and ann fudges selfhelp program archived december   at the wayback machine how ann fudge wants to change yr all from bloomberg businessweek march   a source for the jrankorg bio retrieved june    all mississippi stores had a prominent teen board  for another example of the term retrieved june    a b c d board of directors biography archived june   at the wayback machine council on foreign relations website retrieved june    fortunes first annual look at the women who most influence corporate america by julie creswell reporter associate dina bass fortune october   retrieved june    catalyst inc board list ann fudge is listed as honorary director ao  retrieved june   via jrankorg bio  leadership lessons with ann fudge archived april   at the wayback machine commonwealth institute webpage retrieved may    a b c ann m fudgepermanent dead link economic club of minnesota webpage retrieved may   the new biography for this and the commonwealth institute engagements in  nearly or completely identical did not mention fudges service on the ncfrr  trustees archived july   at the wayback machine brookings webpage retrieved august    a b infosys announces appointment of new members to the board infosys press release june    mishra pankaj nr narayana murthy wants a woman leader on infosys board the economic times june   am ist retrieved june    nacd announces the  directorship   pr newswire press release via marketwatch september    am edt retrieved october    congratulations to the nacd directorship  hall of fame the class of  and people to watch nacd webpage retrieved october    wingfield brianpolitical favorites on obama’s deficit panel archived from the original on august   retrieved july     forbes business in the beltway blog february    pm retrieved july    white house getting to the root causes of our fiscal challenges  simpson alan and erskine bowles the gang of six is our best shot washington post opinion column june   retrieved july    henderson stephen time runs short but gang of six plan is worth pursuing detroit free press july   retrieved july    factbox potential candidates to replace summers reuters september   retrieved november    thrush glenn and kendra marr woman ceo sought for summers job politico september   retrieved november    alden william who will replace larry summers the possible candidates to head white house economic team photos the huffington post september   retrieved november    crfb go big event recap crfb webpage retrieved october    current board members archived october   at the wayback machine state department webpage retrieved april    an office of their own archived december   at the wayback machine bloomberg businessweek march   briefly pr