n’s finance committee in early  fudge was named by president obama to the member national commission on fiscal responsibility and reform a bipartisan panel chaired by former senator alan k simpson rwy and former white house chief of staff erskine bowles d the balance of the panel was three more members appointed by the president six members of the us house of representatives and six members of the us senate the commission first met on april   and had a december report deadline though specific actions based on the report were limited commission members who were also members of congress reappeared in the socalled gang of six in spring and summer  in the debtceilingincrease debate in september  fudge was listed as one of several possible candidates to replace larry summers as director of the national economic council some reports signalled that the white house could be looking for a female executive with business experience to fill the post in september  fudge joined in the committee for a responsible federal budget crfb go big forum crfb along with the new america foundation the concord coalition and the bipartisan policy center discussed the path ahead for the joint select committee on deficit reduction super committee and the reasons it should exceed its mandate fudge also serves on the state departments foreign affairs policy board personal lifeedit as a sophomore at simmons ann married rich fudge before she graduated they had a baby rich jr she had to balance personal and academicprofessional demands from that early stage on her fondest memory from general mills  involved her younger son kevin then  ms fudge had just been made a marketing director the first woman and the first black at that level i came home all excited and was telling my family and he said whats the big deal mom so now instead of one brand you have four you can do that he was right my sons have helped keep things in perspective fudge is also noted for having pursued her career despite the glass ceiling which has been seen to thwart promotion to the top ranks facing women and minorities in the corporate workforce particularly and in regards fudges relatively early moves out of jobs the  business week article also included a sidebar on four other women who left highpowered positions in the corporate world to find a place where they could work on their own terms fudge is currently based in chestnut hill ma she and her husband have five grandchildren awards and honorsedit candace award national coalition of  black women  referencesedit  a b c d ann fudge biography jrankorg retrieved june    a b c d e f g way beyond the glass ceiling by judith h dobrzyski the new york times may   retrieved june   via jrankorg bio  a b c president obama appoints morehouse trustee ann fudge to fiscal commission archived june   at the wayback machine morehouse press release by add seymour jr march   retrieved june    a b ann fudge on making choices the young  rubicam ceo talks about the benefits of stepping away from work and how her priorities changed because of it archived december   at the wayback machine interview with diane brady also act two cover image of ann fudge archived december   at the wayback machine a family portrait archived december   at the wayback machine an assessment of six young  rubicam operations and ann fudges selfhelp program archived december   at the wayback machine how ann fudge wants to change yr all from bloomberg businessweek march   a source for the jrankorg bio retrieved june    all mississippi stores had a prominent teen board  for another example of the term retrieved june    a b c d board of directors biography archived june   at the wayback machine council on foreign relations website retrieved june    fortunes first annual look at the women who most influence corporate america by julie creswell reporter associate dina bass fortune october   retrieved june    catalyst inc board list ann fudge is listed as honorary director ao  retrieved june   