 as a sophomore at simmons ann married rich fudge before she graduated they had a baby rich jr she had to balance personal and academicprofessional demands from that early stage on her fondest memory from general mills  involved her younger son kevin then  ms fudge had just been made a marketing director the first woman and the first black at that level i came home all excited and was telling my family and he said whats the big deal mom so now instead of one brand you have four you can do that he was right my sons have helped keep things in perspective fudge is also noted for having pursued her career despite the glass ceiling which has been seen to thwart promotion to the top ranks facing women and minorities in the corporate workforce particularly and in regards fudges relatively early moves out of jobs the  business week article also included a sidebar on four other women who left highpowered positions in the corporate world to find a place where they could work on their own terms fudge is currently based in chestnut hill ma she and her husband have five grandchildren awards and honorsedit candace award national coalition of  black women  referencesedit  a b c d ann fudge biography jrankorg retrieved june    a b c d e f g way beyond the glass ceiling by judith h dobrzyski the new york times may   retrieved june   via jrankorg bio  a b c president obama appoints morehouse trustee ann fudge to fiscal commission archived june   at the wayback machine morehouse press release by add seymour jr march   retrieved june    a b ann fudge on making choices the young  rubicam ceo talks about the benefits of stepping away from work and how her priorities changed because of it archived december   at the wayback machine interview with diane brady also act two cover image of ann fudge archived december   at the wayback machine a family portrait archived december   at the wayback machine an assessment of six young  rubicam operations and ann fudges selfhelp program archived decem